README.md:15:Generative content is only useful if the world remains fair, finite, and debuggable. This repo separates creative intent from world physics: the Director may invent names, themes, enemies, items, quests, and narration, but it cannot mutate state, change rules, or bypass playability. The schema is the physics boundary; the gauntlet is the shipping gate; artifacts are the receipt.
README.md:43:Layer 1 is trusted TypeScript: movement, combat, status effects, hunger, quests, win/loss, rendering, trace replay, and bots. Layer 2 is untrusted generation: it produces bounded manifests and never state deltas. The gauntlet is the contract between them.
